quran[6]{c,v,t,f}:
48,10,"Those who swore fealty to you, (O Prophet), {1} in fact swore fealty to Allah. The Hand of Allah is above their hands. {2} So whoever breaks his covenant breaks it to his own hurt; and whoever fulfils the covenant that he made with Allah, {3} He will bestow on him a great reward.",footnotes:1:The reference is to the pledge that the Prophet (peace be upon him) took from his companions at Hudaibiyah at the rumor that Uthman had been killed at Makkah. According to some traditions it was a pledge unto death
48,11,"(O Prophet), the bedouins who were left behind say to you: {1} “We were occupied with our goods and families. So ask forgiveness for us.” They say with their tongues what is not in their hearts. {2} Say to them: “Who can be of any avail to you against Allah if He should intend to cause you any harm or confer upon you any benefit?” Allah is well aware of all that you do. {3}",footnotes:1:This has two meanings:|181476:(1) That after your returning to Madinah the excuse that these people will present for not going out with you
48,12,"(But the truth is not what you say.) You had imagined that the Messenger and the believers would never return to their families, and this notion was embellished in your hearts. {1} You harboured an evil thought, and you are an immensely evil people.” {2}",footnotes:1:The word ba-ir (pl. bur in the original) has two meanings:|181477:That is
48,13,"As for those who do not believe in Allah and His Messenger, for such unbelievers We have prepared a Blazing Fire. {1}",footnotes:1:Here
48,14,"To Allah belongs the kingdom of the heavens and the earth. He forgives whom He pleases and chastises whom He pleases. He is Most Forgiving, Most Compassionate. {1}",footnotes:1:The mention of Allah’s being All-Forgiving and All- Merciful
48,15,"When you press forth for the spoils, those who were left behind will say: “Let us accompany you.” {1} They want to change the command of Allah. {2} Say to them (in clear words): “You shall not accompany us. Thus has Allah already said.” {3} Then they will say: “Nay; but you are jealous of us.” The truth is that they understand little.",footnotes:1:Allah’s Word implies the decree that only those people would be allowed to accompany the Prophet (peace be upon him) in the expedition to Khaiber
